{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Compare different effective model potentials"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "from ryd_numerov.rydberg import RydbergState"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Check Rubidium with large n\n",
    "For Rubidium and large quantum numbers n we expect the effective model potentials to be very similar."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Creating wavefunction for model_potential_marinescu_1993\n",
      "Creating wavefunction for model_potential_fei_2009\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "state = RydbergState(\"Rb\", n=40, l=0, j=0.5)\n",
    "\n",
    "states: dict[str, RydbergState] = {}\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "states[\"model_potential_marinescu_1993\"] = RydbergState(state.species, n=state.n, l=state.l, j=state.j)\n",
    "states[\"model_potential_marinescu_1993\"].create_model(potential_type=\"model_potential_marinescu_1993\")\n",
    "\n",
    "states[\"model_potential_fei_2009\"] = RydbergState(state.species, n=state.n, l=state.l, j=state.j)\n",
    "states[\"model_potential_fei_2009\"].create_model(potential_type=\"model_potential_fei_2009\")\n",
    "\n",
    "for label, state in states.items():\n",
    "    print(f\"Creating wavefunction for {label}\")\n",
    "    state.create_wavefunction()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1200x600 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, axs = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 6))\n",
    "\n",
    "for ax in axs:\n",
    "    linestyles = [\"-\", \"--\", \"-.\", \":\"]\n",
    "    for label, state in states.items():\n",
    "        ax.plot(state.grid.z_list, state.wavefunction.w_list, label=label, lw=2, ls=linestyles.pop(0))\n",
    "\n",
    "    ax.legend()\n",
    "    ax.set_xlabel(\"$z$\")\n",
    "    ax.set_ylabel(\"$w(z)$\")\n",
    "\n",
    "axs[1].set_xlim(0, 5)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Big differences for Strontium with small n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "The wavefunction (species=Sr88_singlet n=8, l=0, j=0.0) has some issues:\n",
      "      The maximum of the wavefunction is close to the inner boundary (idmax=92) probably due to inner divergence of the wavefunction. \n",
      "      The wavefunction is negative at the inner boundary (-0.1835397054273211).\n",
      "      The wavefunction has 6.0 nodes, but should have 7 nodes.\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Creating wavefunction for model_potential_marinescu_1993\n",
      "Creating wavefunction for model_potential_fei_2009\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "state = RydbergState(\"Sr88_singlet\", n=8, l=0, j=0)\n",
    "\n",
    "states: dict[str, RydbergState] = {}\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "states[\"model_potential_marinescu_1993\"] = RydbergState(state.species, n=state.n, l=state.l, j=state.j)\n",
    "states[\"model_potential_marinescu_1993\"].create_model(potential_type=\"model_potential_marinescu_1993\")\n",
    "\n",
    "states[\"model_potential_fei_2009\"] = RydbergState(state.species, n=state.n, l=state.l, j=state.j)\n",
    "states[\"model_potential_fei_2009\"].create_model(potential_type=\"model_potential_fei_2009\")\n",
    "\n",
    "for label, state in states.items():\n",
    "    print(f\"Creating wavefunction for {label}\")\n",
    "    state.create_wavefunction()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1200x600 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, axs = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 6))\n",
    "\n",
    "for ax in axs:\n",
    "    linestyles = [\"-\", \"--\", \"-.\", \":\"]\n",
    "    for label, state in states.items():\n",
    "        ax.plot(state.grid.z_list, state.wavefunction.w_list, label=label, lw=2, ls=linestyles.pop(0))\n",
    "\n",
    "    ax.legend()\n",
    "    ax.set_xlabel(\"$z$\")\n",
    "    ax.set_ylabel(\"$w(z)$\")\n",
    "\n",
    "axs[1].set_xlim(0, 5)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  }
